wndwalk
=======
wndwalk is a small virtual desktop navigation tool for Windows.

Tutorial
--------

    [Alt]+[{1..9}]          - switch to another desktop
    [Alt]+[p]               - launch wndmenu (optional)
    [Alt]+[Shift]+[{1..9}]  - send focused window to another desktop
    [Alt]+[Shift]+[Enter]   - launch terminal
    [Alt]+[Shift]+[q]       - log out
    [Alt]+[Shift]+[c]       - close focused window
    [Alt]+[Shift]+[f]       - float focused window
    [Alt]+[Shift]+[m]       - maximize focused window

Requirements
------------
In order to build wndwalk you need Visual Studio Build Tools 2022.

Installation
------------
Open x64 Native Tools Command Prompt for VS 2022.

Afterwards, enter the following command to build wndwalk:

    nmake

Configuration
-------------
The configuration of wndwalk is done by editing config.hpp and (re)compiling the
source code.
